The header and directory data look correct (IWAD=1264 lumps, first entry is PLAYPAL). The real issue is that the VM only loads .text, .data, and .rodata sections - it does NOT load .bss. This means all static variables (including the heap, global counters, function pointers, etc.) are uninitialized. Let me fix this.

{
  "analysis": "The VM doesn't load .bss section. All static/global variables that default to zero (including heap allocator state, zone memory, function pointers) are uninitialized. Need to add BSS clearing in __start or modify VM to handle .bss.",
  "plan": "1. Add _bss_start/_end symbols to linker script. 2. Modify __start to clear BSS before calling main. 3. Rebuild and test.",
  "commands": [
    {"keystrokes": "cat > /app/doomgeneric/doomgeneric/mips.ld << 'EOF'
OUTPUT_FORMAT("elf32-tradlittlemips")
ENTRY(main)
SECTIONS
{
  . = 0x400000;
  .text : { *(.text.startup) *(.text*) }
  .rodata : { *(.rodata*) }
  .data : { *(.data*) }
  .bss : { _bss_start = .; *(.bss*) *(COMMON)
    . = ALIGN(16);
    _bss_end = .;
  }
  _end = .;
}
EOF
", "duration": 0.1},
    {"keystrokes": "cat > /tmp/fix_start.py << 'PYEOF'
data = open('/app/doomgeneric/doomgeneric/doomgeneric_img.c').read()
old = '''void __start(void) __attribute__((section(".text.startup")));
void __start(void) {
  main(0, 0);
  while (1);
}'''
new = '''extern char _bss_start[];
extern char _bss_end[];

void __start(void) __attribute__((section(".text.startup")));
void __start(void) {
  // Clear BSS
  char *p = _bss_start;
  while (p < _bss_end) *p++ = 0;
  main(0, 0);
  while (1);
}'''
data = data.replace(old, new)
open('/app/doomgeneric/doomgeneric/doomgeneric_img.c', 'w').write(data)
print('Done')
PYEOF
", "duration": 0.1},
    {"keystrokes": "python3 /tmp/fix_start.py
", "duration": 0.5},
    {"keystrokes": "grep -A12 '__start' /app/doomgeneric/doomgeneric/doomgeneric_img.c | head -15
", "duration": 0.1}
  ]
}
